  "source": "Emitter oracle (Task 21): a FIXED-parameter (no fit) seeded ISimulatable draw off the REAL RMC.BestFit ARIMAX model with the inline Fourier seasonality term ON (Numerics @ 2a0357a, RMC-BestFit @ c2e6192), dumped via tools/oracle_emitter and reproduced by tools/verify_oracles.py. This pins the v2.0.0 InferSeasonalPeriod change: annual records now infer a DECADAL cycle (OneYear 1 -> 10, ARIMAX.cs:880). The two cases are the same model, parameters and seed on OneYear vs OneMonth, so they differ ONLY through the inferred seasonal period S -- at the pre-v2.0.0 S = 1 the Fourier pair collapses (sin(2*pi*t) == 0, cos(2*pi*t) == 1 at integer t) and the annual draw would flatten onto the no-seasonality stream. Because the parameters are pinned, this isolates the seeded MersenneTwister stream + inverse-CDF + the seasonal mean: the C++/R/Python port reproduces the C# draw bit-identically, so it carries rel 1e-9.",
